    "The largest model, 70B generally outperforms the smaller sizes across all metrics while observing the same phenomenon in mistake insertion, previously discussed in 6.1.",
    "The improvement over smaller sizes may also be attributed to the enhanced accuracy in generating entailment scores for the explanation, analogous to observing greater performance of larger models in NLI tasks.",
    "Llama-13B surprisingly performs worse than its smaller variant, despite having a bigger network.",
    "Moreover, we note that by using SEA-CoT, even a 7B-sized model can generate more interpretable reasoning chains than a 70B model with other baseline prompts.",
